The paper discusses the effectiveness of measuring dimension in the cosparse analysis model, which is a signal processing problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with compressed sensing and matrix completion, which are sub-fields of signal processing, making cs.SP (Signal Processing) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses numerical simulations, which suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms, which may place it under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper mentions applications in computer vision, which may make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
